If you want to further vectorize  the line `B[ax0] = (B[ax0] + B.rf[k.inner.v])` in the code above, you may have to create an intermediate buffer so you can vectorize on `ax0`. This introduces a tradeoff between locality and vectorization.

```python
import tvm

N = 128
V = 8

A = tvm.placeholder((N, N), name='A')
k = tvm.reduce_axis((0, N), name='k')
B = tvm.compute((N,), lambda i : tvm.sum(A[i, k], axis=k), name='B')

s = tvm.create_schedule(B.op)
ko, ki = s[B].split(k, V)
BF = s.rfactor(B, ki)
#s[BF].compute_at(s[B], s[B].op.axis[1])
s[BF].vectorize(s[BF].op.axis[0])

ax0 = s[B].op.axis[0]
k = s[B].op.reduce_axis[0]
ax0, vax0 = s[B].split(ax0, V)
s[B].vectorize(vax0)

print(tvm.lower(s, [A, B], simple_mode=True))
```


```c++
// attr [B.rf] storage_scope = "global"
allocate B.rf[float32x8 * 8 * 16]
produce B.rf {
  for (i, 0, 128) {
    B.rf[ramp(i, 128, 8)] = x8(0.000000f)
    for (k.outer, 0, 16) {
      B.rf[ramp(i, 128, 8)] = (B.rf[ramp(i, 128, 8)] + A[ramp((((i*16) + k.outer)*8), 1, 8)])
    }
  }
}
produce B {
  for (ax0.outer, 0, 16) {
    B[ramp((ax0.outer*8), 1, 8)] = x8(0.000000f)
    for (k.inner.v, 0, 8) {
      B[ramp((ax0.outer*8), 1, 8)] = (B[ramp((ax0.outer*8), 1, 8)] + B.rf[ramp(((ax0.outer + (k.inner.v*16))*8), 1, 8)])
    }
  }
}
```

@nhynes don't think `#[derive(Builder)]]` can add the *proper* fields in builder struct needed for `Function`. It is merely for very common type of builders. Currently, `derive_builder` only uses the fields of the underlying struct, but the rather minimal signature of the current `function::Builder` is

```
pub struct Builder<'a> {
    pub func: Option<Function>,
    pub arg_buf: Option<Box<[TVMArgValue<'a>]>>,
    pub ret_buf: Option<Box<[TVMRetValue]>>,
}
```
with completely different fields, in particular `arg_buf` and `ret_buf`. So my conclusion is that the `derive_builder` is not mature enough to handle our case.

*Side note*: In my code, I've pretty much followed [`std::process::Command`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/process/struct.Command.html) construct.

